Package: RSurvivEHR
Type: Package
Title: Survival Analysis on Electronic Health Records via SurvivEHR
Version: 0.8.2
Authors@R: person(given = "Pedro", family = "Cardoso", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "p.cardoso@exeter.ac.uk", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1014-9058"))
Description: An R interface to SurvivEHR, a transformer-based survival model
    for longitudinal Electronic Health Record (EHR) data. Build a vocabulary
    from clinical event sequences, pre-train a competing-risk or single-risk
    survival backbone, fine-tune on labelled outcomes (single-risk or
    competing-risk), and predict cumulative-incidence curves — all from plain
    R data frames. Input data frames use consistent lowercase column names
    (`patient_id`, `event`, `age`, `value`; `patient_id`, `target_event`,
    `target_age`); uppercase aliases are accepted for backward compatibility.
    Supports biomarker values alongside discrete events, leakage-free cohort
    construction helpers, and frequency-ordered vocabularies. The Python
    backend is vendored inside the package and managed automatically via
    'reticulate'.
